                </div>
                <p>The excitement around the <span class="font-weight-700">Suzuki GSX-8S</span> has been building for a while, and the latest reports suggest a concrete timeline for its arrival. While an official announcement from Suzuki is still pending, industry sources indicate that the <span class="font-weight-700">GSX-8S</span> is expected to be launched in India around <span class="font-weight-700">October 2025. </span> This timeline is perfectly poised to capture the attention of Indian buyers during the festive season, a period when two-wheeler sales traditionally peak. </p>
                <p>As for the price, the <span class="font-weight-700">Suzuki GSX-8S </span>is likely to be positioned in the premium middleweight segment. Based on its global pricing and the features it offers, the ex-showroom price is anticipated to be in the range of <span class="font-weight-700">₹10.00 Lakh to ₹11.00 Lakh. </span> It is worth noting that this is a premium price tag for a bike in this class, and the final on-road price will be significantly higher, depending on the state and city. However, considering the advanced technology and the brand reputation that comes with it, this price is a testament to the bike's premium positioning. </p>
                <h3 class="subheading">The Heart of the Beast: Specifications</h3>
