                <p>The <span class="font-weight-700">Suzuki GSX-8S </span>is not just about a powerful engine and a great chassis; it's also a technology-laden machine. It comes with a suite of electronic rider aids that are part of the <span class="font-weight-700">Suzuki Intelligent Ride System (SIRS). </span> These features are designed to make the bike safer, more fun, and more manageable for riders of all skill levels. The bike is equipped with a Ride-by-wire electronic throttle, which allows for precise and smooth power delivery. </p>
                <p>The bike's electronics suite includes a three-mode Suzuki Drive Mode Selector (SDMS), which allows the rider to choose from three different engine maps (A, B, and C) to suit different riding conditions. It also features a four-mode (including off) Suzuki Traction Control System (STCS) that prevents wheel spin and ensures confident riding, especially on low-grip surfaces. The bike also gets Suzuki's Easy Start System and Low RPM Assist, which are great for city riding and make it easier to manage the bike at low speeds. </p>
